{"type":"text","timestamp":1775845291412,"sessionID":"ses_2875fec33ffefhYBum3nJkteaU","part":{"id":"prt_d78a0b194001gSygLMfGde4xvz","messageID":"msg_d78a0a663001KO1eDwExwaDQ4H","sessionID":"ses_2875fec33ffefhYBum3nJkteaU","type":"text","text":"Now I have a good understanding of the project. Let me create the proposal.md file for AR-007 — K8s Reconciler 控制器. Based on the client-go documentation provided and the existing codebase structure, I'll write a comprehensive proposal.","time":{"start":1775845291410,"end":1775845291410}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845371803,"sessionID":"ses_2875fec33ffefhYBum3nJkteaU","part":{"id":"prt_d78a0b595001CUJYQ8rxbwZY4E","messageID":"msg_d78a0a663001KO1eDwExwaDQ4H","sessionID":"ses_2875fec33ffefhYBum3nJkteaU","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_468684d16c3b45bba364b28f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/proposal.md","content":"# AR-007: K8s Reconciler 控制器\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis proposal defines the design and implementation of a Kubernetes-native Reconciler controller for the AgentCube project. The Reconciler controller watches `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` CRDs and ensures the actual cluster state matches the desired state specified in the CR specs. The goal is to:\n\n1. **Implement the Kubernetes Operator Pattern** — Use controller-runtime to build event-driven reconcilers that react to CRD changes\n2. **Automate sandbox lifecycle management** — Create, update, and delete sandbox pods based on CRD spec changes\n3. **Maintain CRD status consistency** — Continuously reconcile CRD status with actual sandbox pod state\n4. **Provide extensible reconciliation hooks** — Allow future extensions for custom lifecycle logic\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager` (reconciler package)  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** L\n\nThis AR covers:\n\n- **In scope:**\n  - Reconciler implementation for `AgentRuntime` CRD\n  - Reconciler implementation for `CodeInterpreter` CRD\n  - Integration with existing client-go types, listers, and informers\n  - Sandbox pod creation and lifecycle management\n  - CRD status update logic\n  - Unit tests and integration tests for reconcilers\n  - Controller manager setup and initialization\n\n- **Out of scope:**\n  - HTTP API changes to WorkloadManager (AR-004)\n  - Router or session routing logic\n  - Redis persistence layer changes\n  - Volcano scheduler integration (future AR)\n\n## Current State Analysis\n\n### Existing Infrastructure\n\nThe codebase already has the following components that the Reconciler will leverage:\n\n1. **Generated client-go code** (`deployment/client-go.md`):\n   - Typed clients: `AgentRuntimeInterface`, `CodeInterpreterInterface`\n   - Informers: `SharedInformerFactory`, `AgentRuntimeInformer`, `CodeInterpreterInformer`\n   - Listers: `AgentRuntimeLister`, `CodeInterpreterLister`\n   - Fake clients for testing\n\n2. **CRD types** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`):\n   - `AgentRuntime` with `Spec` and `Status` fields\n   - `CodeInterpreter` with `Spec` and `Status` fields\n   - Shared types: `ResourceQuota`, `NetworkPolicy`, `ContainerSpec`\n\n3. **WorkloadManager HTTP service** (`pkg/workloadmanager/`):\n   - Existing HTTP handlers for CRUD operations\n   - Gin-based server framework\n   - Configuration management\n\n### Issues Identified\n\n1. **No reconciliation loop** — Current WorkloadManager only responds to HTTP requests, does not react to cluster state changes\n2. **Status drift** — CRD status may become stale if sandbox pods change outside HTTP API\n3. **Manual lifecycle management** — No automatic cleanup or recovery of failed sandboxes\n4. **No event-driven architecture** — Cannot trigger actions on pod events (e.g., restart, delete)\n\n## Proposed Changes\n\n### 1. Controller Architecture\n\n```\nController Manager\n  ├─ AgentRuntime Reconciler\n  │   ├─ Watches: AgentRuntime CRD\n  │   ├─ Watches: Sandbox Pods (owned by AgentRuntime)\n  │   └─ Reconciles: Spec → Pod creation/update, Status sync\n  └─ CodeInterpreter Reconciler\n      ├─ Watches: CodeInterpreter CRD\n      ├─ Watches: Sandbox Pods (owned by CodeInterpreter)\n      └─ Reconciles: Spec → Pod creation/update, Status sync\n```\n\n**Key components:**\n\n| Component | Responsibility |\n|-----------|----------------|\n| **Controller Manager** | Initializes reconcilers, manages shared informers, handles graceful shutdown |\n| **Reconciler** | Implements `Reconcile(ctx, req)` for a specific CRD |\n| **Sandbox Processor** | Creates/updates/deletes sandbox pods from CRD spec |\n| **Status Updater** | Updates CRD status based on pod state |\n| **Owner Reference Manager** | Sets owner references for garbage collection |\n\n### 2. Directory Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── reconciler/\n│   ├── manager.go           # Controller manager initialization\n│   ├── agentruntime_reconciler.go  # AgentRuntime reconciler logic\n│   ├── codeinterpreter_reconciler.go # CodeInterpreter reconciler logic\n│   ├── sandbox_processor.go  # Sandbox pod creation/update logic\n│   └── status_updater.go    # CRD status update utilities\n├── controller/\n│   ├── controller.go        # Base controller interface (optional)\n│   └── metrics.go           # Prometheus metrics for controllers\n└── ... (existing files)\n```\n\n### 3. Reconciler Implementation Pattern\n\n```go\n// pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime_reconciler.go\n\ntype AgentRuntimeReconciler struct {\n    clientset    versioned.Interface\n    client       kubernetes.Interface\n    agentRuntimeLister listers.AgentRuntimeLister\n    podLister    corelisters.PodLister\n    recorder     record.EventRecorder\n}\n\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req controllerruntime.Request) (controllerruntime.Result, error) {\n    log := log.FromContext(ctx)\n    \n    // 1. Fetch AgentRuntime\n    agentRuntime, err := r.agentRuntimeLister.AgentRuntimes(req.Namespace).Get(req.Name)\n    if err != nil {\n        if k8s_errors.IsNotFound(err) {\n            log.Info(\"AgentRuntime not found, skipping\")\n            return controllerruntime.Result{}, nil\n        }\n        return controllerruntime.Result{}, err\n    }\n    \n    // 2. Check deletion timestamp (handle deletion)\n    if !agentRuntime.DeletionTimestamp.IsZero() {\n        return r.reconcileDeletion(ctx, agentRuntime)\n    }\n    \n    // 3. Reconcile sandbox pod\n    pod, err := r.reconcileSandboxPod(ctx, agentRuntime)\n    if err != nil {\n        return controllerruntime.Result{}, err\n    }\n    \n    // 4. Update status\n    if err := r.updateStatus(ctx, agentRuntime, pod); err != nil {\n        return controllerruntime.Result{}, err\n    }\n    \n    return controllerruntime.Result{}, nil\n}\n\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) reconcileSandboxPod(ctx context.Context, ar *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) (*corev1.Pod, error) {\n    // Check if pod exists\n    existingPod, err := r.getOwnedPod(ctx, ar)\n    if err != nil && !k8s_errors.IsNotFound(err) {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    \n    if k8s_errors.IsNotFound(err) {\n        // Create new pod\n        pod := buildSandboxPod(ar)\n        return r.client.CoreV1().Pods(ar.Namespace).Create(ctx, pod, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n    }\n    \n    // Check if pod needs update\n    if needsUpdate(existingPod, ar) {\n        updatedPod := buildSandboxPod(ar)\n        updatedPod.ResourceVersion = existingPod.ResourceVersion\n        return r.client.CoreV1().Pods(ar.Namespace).Update(ctx, updatedPod, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n    }\n    \n    return existingPod, nil\n}\n```\n\n### 4. Controller Manager Setup\n\n```go\n// pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go\n\ntype ControllerManager struct {\n    config          *rest.Config\n    clientset       versioned.Interface\n    informerFactory informers.SharedInformerFactory\n    reconcilers     []Reconciler\n    ctx             context.Context\n    cancel          context.CancelFunc\n}\n\nfunc NewControllerManager(config *rest.Config) (*ControllerManager, error) {\n    clientset, err := versioned.NewForConfig(config)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to create clientset: %w\", err)\n    }\n    \n    informerFactory := informers.NewSharedInformerFactory(clientset, 10*time.Minute)\n    \n    return &ControllerManager{\n        config:          config,\n        clientset:       clientset,\n        informerFactory: informerFactory,\n        reconcilers:     make([]Reconciler, 0),\n    }, nil\n}\n\nfunc (m *ControllerManager) AddReconciler(r Reconciler) {\n    m.reconcilers = append(m.reconcilers, r)\n}\n\nfunc (m *ControllerManager) Start() error {\n    stopCh := m.ctx.Done()\n    \n    // Start informers\n    m.informerFactory.Start(stopCh)\n    \n    // Wait for cache sync\n    synced := m.informerFactory.WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)\n    for resourceType, ok := range synced {\n        if !ok {\n            return fmt.Errorf(\"informer failed to sync: %v\", resourceType)\n        }\n    }\n    \n    // Start reconcilers\n    for _, r := range m.reconcilers {\n        go r.Run(m.ctx)\n    }\n    \n    <-m.ctx.Done()\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### 5. Watch Configuration\n\nThe reconcilers will watch the following resources:\n\n| Reconciler | Watches | Triggers Reconcile |\n|------------|---------|-------------------|\n| **AgentRuntime** | `AgentRuntime` CRD | Create, Update, Delete |\n| | `Pod` (owned by AgentRuntime) | Create, Update, Delete |\n| **CodeInterpreter** | `CodeInterpreter` CRD | Create, Update, Delete |\n| | `Pod` (owned by CodeInterpreter) | Create, Update, Delete |\n\n**Owner reference pattern:**\n\n```go\nfunc buildSandboxPod(ar *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) *corev1.Pod {\n    return &corev1.Pod{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      fmt.Sprintf(\"sandbox-%s\", ar.Name),\n            Namespace: ar.Namespace,\n            OwnerReferences: []metav1.OwnerReference{\n                *metav1.NewControllerRef(ar, runtimev1alpha1.SchemeGroupVersion.WithKind(\"AgentRuntime\")),\n            },\n            Labels: map[string]string{\n                \"agentcube.volcano.sh/runtime\": ar.Name,\n                \"agentcube.volcano.sh/type\":    \"agentruntime\",\n            },\n        },\n        Spec: buildPodSpec(ar),\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 6. Status Update Logic\n\n```go\n// pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/status_updater.go\n\nfunc (r *AgentRuntimeReconciler) updateStatus(ctx context.Context, ar *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, pod *corev1.Pod) error {\n    if pod == nil {\n        ar.Status.Phase = runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimePhasePending\n        ar.Status.Conditions = []runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeCondition{\n            {\n                Type:               runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeConditionSandboxCreated,\n                Status:             corev1.ConditionFalse,\n                Reason:             \"PodNotFound\",\n                Message:            \"Sandbox pod not found\",\n                LastTransitionTime: metav1.Now(),\n            },\n        }\n    } else {\n        ar.Status.Phase = mapPodPhaseToRuntimePhase(pod.Status.Phase)\n        ar.Status.SandboxRef = &corev1.ObjectReference{\n            Name:      pod.Name,\n            Namespace: pod.Namespace,\n            UID:       pod.UID,\n        }\n        ar.Status.Conditions = buildConditionsFromPod(pod)\n    }\n    \n    _, err := r.clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(ar.Namespace).UpdateStatus(ctx, ar, metav1.UpdateOptions{})\n    return err\n}\n\nfunc mapPodPhaseToRuntimePhase(podPhase corev1.PodPhase) runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimePhase {\n    switch podPhase {\n    case corev1.PodPending:\n        return runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimePhasePending\n    case corev1.PodRunning:\n        return runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimePhaseRunning\n    case corev1.PodFailed:\n        return runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimePhaseFailed\n    case corev1.PodSucceeded:\n        return runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimePhaseRunning\n    default:\n        return runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimePhasePending\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 7. Integration with Existing WorkloadManager\n\nThe Reconciler controller will run alongside the existing HTTP server:\n\n```go\n// cmd/workload-manager/main.go\n\nfunc main() {\n    // Load config\n    config := loadConfig()\n    \n    // Create controller manager\n    controllerMgr, err := reconciler.NewControllerManager(config.KubeConfig)\n    if err != nil {\n        log.Fatalf(\"Failed to create controller manager: %v\", err)\n    }\n    \n    // Create reconcilers\n    arReconciler := reconciler.NewAgentRuntimeReconciler(...)\n    ciReconciler := reconciler.NewCodeInterpreterReconciler(...)\n    \n    controllerMgr.AddReconciler(arReconciler)\n    controllerMgr.AddReconciler(ciReconciler)\n    \n    // Create HTTP server\n    server, err := workloadmanager.NewServer(config)\n    if err != nil {\n        log.Fatalf(\"Failed to create server: %v\", err)\n    }\n    \n    // Start both\n    ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(context.Background())\n    defer cancel()\n    \n    errCh := make(chan error, 2)\n    \n    go func() {\n        if err := controllerMgr.Start(); err != nil {\n            errCh <- fmt.Errorf(\"controller manager failed: %w\", err)\n        }\n    }()\n    \n    go func() {\n        if err := server.Run(ctx); err != nil {\n            errCh <- fmt.Errorf(\"HTTP server failed: %w\", err)\n        }\n    }()\n    \n    // Wait for errors or shutdown signal\n    select {\n    case err := <-errCh:\n        log.Fatalf(\"Error: %v\", err)\n    case <-ctx.Done():\n        log.Info(\"Shutting down...\")\n    }\n}\n```\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files to Create\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go` | Controller manager initialization and lifecycle |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime_reconciler.go` | AgentRuntime reconciliation logic |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/codeinterpreter_reconciler.go` | CodeInterpreter reconciliation logic |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/sandbox_processor.go` | Sandbox pod build/create/update logic |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/status_updater.go` | Status update utilities |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/agentruntime_reconciler_test.go` | AgentRuntime reconciler unit tests |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/codeinterpreter_reconciler_test.go` | CodeInterpreter reconciler unit tests |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager_test.go` | Controller manager tests |\n\n### Files to Modify\n\n| File | Changes | Impact |\n|------|---------|--------|\n| `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` | Add controller manager initialization | Medium - startup logic changes |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/server.go` | May need to share clientset/informers | Low - dependency injection |\n| `go.mod` | Add controller-runtime dependency | Low - new dependency |\n\n### Dependencies\n\nAdd to `go.mod`:\n\n```go\nrequire (\n    sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime v0.21.0\n    k8s.io/client-go v0.34.1\n    k8s.io/apimachinery v0.34.1\n    k8s.io/api v0.34.1\n)\n```\n\n### Backward Compatibility\n\n- **HTTP API unchanged** — Existing clients continue to work\n- **CRD schema unchanged** — No breaking changes to `AgentRuntime` or `CodeInterpreter`\n- **Informers shared** — Reconciler uses existing informer infrastructure\n\n### Testing Impact\n\n- **Unit tests** — Mock clientset and listers for reconciler tests\n- **Integration tests** — Use envtest (controller-runtime testing framework)\n- **E2E tests** — Extend existing E2E suite to verify reconciliation\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: Use controller-runtime Manager\n\nUse `controller-runtime`'s built-in `Manager` instead of custom controller manager.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Built-in health checks, metrics, leader election\n- Standard pattern in Kubernetes ecosystem\n- Less boilerplate code\n\n**Cons:**\n- Tighter coupling to controller-runtime\n- May conflict with existing Gin server\n- More complex initialization\n\n**Decision:** Use custom manager for now (simpler integration with existing HTTP server). Revisit controller-runtime Manager in future if needed.\n\n### Alternative 2: Separate Controller Binary\n\nRun reconciler as a separate binary (`cmd/controller/main.go`) instead of integrating with WorkloadManager.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Clear separation of concerns\n- Independent scaling\n- Easier to reason about\n\n**Cons:**\n- More complex deployment (2 deployments vs 1)\n- Duplicated clientset/informer initialization\n- More complex debugging\n\n**Decision:** Integrate with WorkloadManager for simplicity. Separate binary can be considered if scaling becomes an issue.\n\n### Alternative 3: Use WorkloadManager HTTP Hooks\n\nTrigger reconciliation from HTTP handlers instead of watches.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Simpler implementation\n- No informer overhead\n\n**Cons:**\n- No event-driven reconciliation\n- Status drift possible\n- Cannot react to external changes (e.g., pod deletion)\n\n**Decision:** Reject — defeats the purpose of Kubernetes operator pattern.\n\n### Alternative 4: Use Informer Event Handlers Directly\n\nUse raw informer event handlers instead of reconcile loop pattern.\n\n**Pros:**\n- Lower latency (no reconcile queue)\n- Simpler for simple use cases\n\n**Cons:**\n- Harder to handle errors and retries\n- No built-in rate limiting\n- More complex state management\n\n**Decision:** Use reconcile pattern — better error handling and retry semantics.\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Add controller-runtime dependency to `go.mod`\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/reconciler/manager.go`\n- [ ] Implement `AgentRuntimeReconciler`\n- [ ] Implement `CodeInterpreterReconciler`\n- [ ] Implement sandbox pod builder/processor\n- [ ] Implement status updater\n- [ ] Add owner reference management\n- [ ] Write unit tests for reconcilers\n- [ ] Write integration tests with envtest\n- [ ] Update `cmd/workload-manager/main.go` to start controller\n- [ ] Update documentation (`deployment/spec.md`)\n- [ ] Add Prometheus metrics for reconciliation (optional)\n- [ ] Add leader election for HA (optional, future)\n\n## Future Considerations\n\n1. **Leader Election** — For high-availability deployments, add leader election to prevent duplicate reconciliation\n2. **Rate Limiting** — Tune reconcile rate limiting to prevent API server overload\n3. **Finalizers** — Add finalizers for complex cleanup logic (e.g., external resource deletion)\n4. **Webhook Integration** — Add validating/mutating webhooks for spec validation\n5. **Metrics & Observability** — Export reconciliation metrics (reconcile duration, error rate, queue depth)\n6. **External Resources** — Support for external resources (e.g., cloud sandboxes) via provider interface\n7. **Horizontal Pod Autoscaler** — Support auto-scaling sandboxes based on load\n\n## References\n\n- [controller-runtime documentation](https://book.kubebuilder.io/cronjob-tutorial/controller-overview.html)\n- [Kubernetes Operator Pattern](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/operator/)\n- [Client-go documentation](deployment/client-go.md)\n- [WorkloadManager design](pkg/workloadmanager/design.md)\n- [Deployment spec](deployment/spec.md)\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go\">\nERROR [67:27] undefined: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInformer\nERROR [75:27] undefined: runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterInformer\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/workloadmanager/routes.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":66,"character":26},"end":{"line":66,"character":46}},"severity":1,"code":"UndeclaredImportedName","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#UndeclaredImportedName"},"source":"compiler","message":"undefined: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeInformer"},{"range":{"start":{"line":74,"character":26},"end":{"line":74,"character":49}},"severity":1,"code":"UndeclaredImportedName","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/internal/typesinternal#UndeclaredImportedName"},"source":"compiler","message":"undefined: runtimev1alpha1.CodeInterpreterInformer"}],"/home/dsj/bench